HERBARIUM OF THE UNIVERSITY OF NORTH CAROLINA
*Galax urceolata* (Poir.) Brummitt
n = 6 based on average guard cell area
Guy L. Nesom, 1975

Herbarium
University of Wisconsin
Rock County Campus
Janesville, Wisconsin 53545
*Galax aphylla* L.

VIRGINIA: Plants of a mountain bog of southwestern
Virginia.

1. Shaded wet area with sphagnum along small
stream in rhododendron thicket.
2. Edge of small pond.
3. Open flat area surrounded by *Tsuga canadensis*,
*Rhododendron maximum*, *Magnolia fraseri*, etc.

North of Virginia Forest Service trail at top of
East River Mountain, 1 mile east of state road
662, Tazewell County. Elevation: ca. 3400 ft.

Lytton J. Musselman  28 July 1969
